## Database Schema

### Tables

#### User

The `user` table stores information about registered users.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description               |
|-------------|-----------|---------------------------|
| id          | INT       | Unique user identifier    |
| email       | VARCHAR   | User's email address      |
| password    | VARCHAR   | User's password (hashed)  |
| name        | VARCHAR   | User's name               |
| created_at  | TIMESTAMP | Date and time of creation |

#### Post

The `post` table stores notes shared by users.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description               |
|-------------|-----------|---------------------------|
| id          | INT       | Unique note identifier    |
| title       | VARCHAR   | Title of the note         |
| content     | TEXT      | Content of the note       |
| pdate       | TIMESTAMP | Date and time of posting  |
| uid         | INT       | User ID who posted the note|

### Database Details

- **Database Name:** enotes
- **DBMS:** MySQL
- **Connection Details:** localhost:3306 (or as per your configuration)
- **Username:** (Your database username)
- **Password:** (Your database password)






